<node id="Aedes aegypti">
  <data key="d0">Aedes aegypti</data>
  <data key="d1">creature</data>
  <data key="d2">Aedes aegypti is a mosquito species that was targeted for elimination using a community-based control strategy.&lt;SEP&gt;Aedes aegypti is a species of mosquito whose population was eliminated in 40 out of 46 communes in northern and central Vietnam through community-based control methods.&lt;SEP&gt;Aedes aegypti is a species of mosquito that serves as a vector for various diseases, including dengue fever and Zika virus.&lt;SEP&gt;Aedes aegypti is a mosquito species responsible for transmitting diseases.&lt;SEP&gt;Aedes aegypti is the primary vector of dengue viruses, targeted by biological control measures involving copepods.&lt;SEP&gt;Aedes aegypti is a mosquito species that transmits various diseases including dengue, yellow fever, and chikungunya viruses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-150b561d4dd47ec0ef54f8c210978655&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8f8704987d6b587388b0e5aace9ebef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae4a9d25675889bda3f33444944f8774&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c6fa496f303accae9be7d0ff7aeaa8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f67b4135b81382ee1dfd5329983fe84&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cecc1574e3d38e1c2b8f29466bffcf9d</data>
